RSM322 was similar to that of RSM222; pretty easy to do well in the course if you put in the effort. Professor Kwan was more of a facilitator, didnt't really lecture at all but gave lots of hints for both the assignments and tests! you just gotta study from the slides and you're good.

Overall, she is a nice prof. She does not go through all the materials, but she tries to emphasize on the important points. The midterm and final were fair and her marking criteria is clear. She also creates a lot of opportunity for participation marks.

rComments: Professor Kwan is a very dry/boring lecturer. She is a soft speaker and is sometimes hard to hear. I found this class exceptionally boring, however, it is very useful for those pursuing accounting. If she likes you, she will provide some life advice and networking help on the side. She grades fairly, with the class average being a B.

Professor Amy Kwan is by far one of the most caring and inspiring instructors at the University of Toronto. She genuinely cares about each and every student, and wants you to truly understand the material you're learning in an effective and useful way. She is very open to feedback and inspires her students.
Amy brings in lots of real life examples from her work. It makes the course so much more practical. She wants her students to succeed. Amy is a great prof.
participation really matters and if u dont participate she will just give u a really low mark
Nice person but the lectures are very dry. She did try to make it a little bit more interesting with some videos, but it was still quite boring. Course isn't very hard if you try.
